This paper deals with optimization and decision-making tasks in the context of neural network design, hyper-parameter optimization, and simulation-based optimization tasks. These tasks are typically encountered in the fields of machine learning, artificial intelligence, and control systems, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.SY. Additionally, the paper involves the use of quasi-random designs and low-discrepancy point sets, which are commonly used in the field of computational statistics and optimization, covered by the arXiv sub-category cs.DS. Therefore, the most likely arXiv sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.DS, in that order.
